alerts.title: Wind Advisory for Multnomah, OR
alerts.description:
...WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 4 PM THIS AFTERNOON TO
6 AM PST THURSDAY FOR THE GREATER PORTLAND AND VANCOUVER METRO
AREAS...THE LOWER COLUMBIA...AND THE INTERSTATE 5 CORRIDOR IN
COWLITZ COUNTY...
* WINDS: SOUTH WINDS 20 TO 30 MPH WITH GUSTS TO 45 MPH. GUSTS TO
50 MPH POSSIBLE IN THE LOWER COWLITZ RIVER VALLEY.
* NEAR THE GORGE: EAST WINDS 20 TO 30 MPH WITH GUSTS TO 40 MPH...
SHIFTING SOUTH WITH GUSTS TO 45 MPH AROUND 7 PM THIS EVENING
THEN CONTINUING FOR THE REMAINDER OF THE NIGHT.
* TIMING: BEGINNING LATE THIS AFTERNOON AND CONTINUE OVERNIGHT
TONIGHT. PEAK WINDS ARE EXPECTED FROM AROUND 8 PM TONIGHT
THROUGH 4 AM EARLY THURSDAY MORNING.
* LOCATIONS INCLUDE: ST. HELENS...HILLSBORO...PORTLAND...OREGON
CITY...GRESHAM...LONGVIEW...KELSO...VANCOUVER...BATTLE
GROUND...WASHOUGAL
* IMPACTS: EXPECT LOCALIZED TREE DAMAGE AND POWER DISRUPTIONS.
THIS EVENT HAS THE POTENTIAL TO CAUSE SOME TREES TO FALL.
FALLING TREES OR LIMBS CAN BE DEADLY. TRAVEL WILL BE DIFFICULT
AT TIMES...ESPECIALLY FOR TRUCKS...TRAILERS...AND OTHER HIGH
PROFILE VEHICLES.
